===date:Tue Feb  4 23:58:10 2003
===message:The French and Indian War was essentially a European war that spilled over onto North America.  England and France had been fighting for centures before North America was discovered by Europe and colonized.  The colonies were pulled into this conflict by thier parent nations, England and France, otherwise they man well have been content to exist in the New World in harmoney.  In essence, England brought troops over to capture the French claims in North America as part of the war they had been waging in Europe, and then wanted the colonies to help fight in it and help pay for it.  All the while letting the British citizenry believe that the war was won solely by the British professional soldiers as if the colonies had no part in the victory.
=========yorg=========
